text: Brigadier General Ratu Epeli Nailatikau, CF, LVO, OBE, MSD, KStJ, (born 5 July 1941) is a Fijian chief and politician. He became the President of Fiji on 5 November 2009.Nailatikau sworn in as Fiji's new President. News.xinhuanet.com (2009-11-05). Retrieved on 2012-05-04. He left office in 2015. In 2019, he became the 2nd Speaker of the Parliament. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:Living people Category:Ambassadors Category:Generals Category:Oceanic military people Category:Presidents of Fiji
